Subject: [PATCH 10/10] add new files: kernel/agent_namespaces.c, headers, tracepoints

This patch is a placeholder.  The new files live in ../kernel/,
../include/linux/, ../include/uapi/linux/, ../include/trace/events/
within this vendor-patch directory and are copied into the kernel tree
verbatim by scripts/build.sh before the numbered diffs are applied.

  kernel/agent_namespaces.c
  include/linux/agent_namespaces.h
  include/uapi/linux/agent_namespaces.h
  include/trace/events/agent_ns.h

A real `git format-patch` series would include these as full-file
additions; the split-out form is friendlier for editing and rebasing
during the wintermute kernel bumps that this PRD calls "the maintenance
cost the user accepts."

